This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to analyze trunk sway data for balance evaluation, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the study involves the use of computer vision techniques to extract features from the trunk sway data, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The study also involves the use of neural networks for classification, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the study involves the use of technology to improve healthcare outcomes, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
